    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Alert on a key metric with HTTP / REST API and Microsoft Teams with instant alerts\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAlert on a key metric with HTTP / REST API and Microsoft Teams with instant alerts. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual risk monitoring is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Fetch Current Metrics → Compute Severity Signals → Grade Severity Tier → Just Record (Info) → Merge Tier Outcomes\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating risk monitoring in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "6acf91d4-eb89-4073-5b0b-708faf87c251",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your risk monitoring process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
